  "text": "The G1 garbage collector implements a concurrent marking and mixed collection cycle in openjdk/jdk. The cycle consists of several interconnected phases:\n\n## 1. Concurrent Mark Start Trigger\n\nThe concurrent marking cycle is triggered via `G1ConcurrentMark::post_concurrent_mark_start()` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.cpp), which activates SATB (Snapshot-At-The-Beginning) marking queues globally across all threads by calling `satb_mq_set.set_active_all_threads(true)`. This initiates weak reference discovery through the reference processor. The corresponding thread orchestration is handled by `G1ConcurrentMarkThread` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMarkThread.hpp), which manages the concurrent marking lifecycle through phases such as `phase_scan_root_regions()` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMarkThread.cpp).\n\n## 2. SATB Marking Queue Processing\n\nThe SATB (Snapshot-At-The-Beginning) marking system is implemented in src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/satbMarkQueue.hpp and satbMarkQueue.cpp. During the concurrent cycle start, the `SATBMarkQueueSet` manages queues for each thread, which record old reference values before objects are modified. G1-specific SATB queue handling is in src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1SATBMarkQueueSet.cpp, where the `requires_marking()` function (line 82-96) filters SATB entries to determine which objects require marking by checking if they were allocated before marking started (via TAMS - Top At Mark Start). Entries below TAMS must be processed; entries at or above TAMS are implicitly marked or already reclaimed.\n\n## 3. Root Region Scanning and Marking\n\n`G1ConcurrentMark::scan_root_regions()` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.cpp, line 1074) performs the initial concurrent scanning of survivor regions and other root regions. This phase runs `G1CMRootRegionScanTask` with concurrent workers. Following root scanning, `mark_from_roots()` (line 1145) kicks off the main marking phase where `G1CMTask` instances (defined in src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.hpp, line 728) scan heap regions and follow object references using task queues and the mark bitmap. Tasks process entries from SATB buffers and bitmap scans, marking reachable objects.\n\n## 4. Remembered Set Scanning\n\nRemembered set management is coordinated through `G1RemSet` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1RemSet.hpp), which uses `G1RemSetScanState` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1RemSet.cpp, line 89) to track scanning progress across regions. Each heap region maintains a `G1HeapRegionRemSet` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1HeapRegionRemSet.hpp, line 42), which encapsulates remembered set information as a `G1CardSet` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CardSet.hpp). The card set uses efficient memory structures managed by `G1CardSetMemory` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CardSetMemory.hpp) to track inter-region references. During concurrent marking, remembered sets are rebuilt and maintain tracking state using `G1RemSetTrackingPolicy` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1RemSetTrackingPolicy.hpp), which determines which regions need remembered set updates.\n\n## 5. Mixed Collection Region Selection\n\nAfter concurrent marking completes, regions are selected for mixed collection through `G1CollectionSetCandidates` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectionSetCandidates.hpp, line 205), which maintains a prioritized list of old generation regions for potential evacuation. The selection process is executed by `G1CollectionSetChooser::build()` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectionSetChooser.cpp, line 262), which leverages `G1BuildCandidateRegionsTask` to identify high-value regions based on reclaimable garbage. Regions are sorted by reclaimable bytes and then pruned according to `G1HeapWastePercent`. Selected regions transition the collector state to `in_mixed_phase()` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectorState.hpp, line 100), enabling mixed collections that evacuate both young and selected old regions.\n\n## Summary of Key Implementation Files\n\n- **Concurrent Mark Control**: src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.{hpp,cpp} and g1ConcurrentMarkThread.{hpp,cpp}\n- **SATB Processing**: src/hotspot/share/gc/shared/satbMarkQueue.{hpp,cpp} and g1SATBMarkQueueSet.{hpp,cpp}\n- **Marking Tasks**: src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1ConcurrentMark.hpp (G1CMTask) and g1OopClosures.{hpp,inline.hpp}\n- **Remembered Set Infrastructure**: src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1RemSet.{hpp,cpp}, g1HeapRegionRemSet.{hpp,cpp}, g1CardSet.{hpp,cpp}, and g1CardSetMemory.{hpp,cpp}\n- **Mixed Collection Selection**: src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1CollectionSetCandidates.{hpp,cpp}, g1CollectionSetChooser.{hpp,cpp}, and g1CollectionSet.{hpp,cpp}\n\nThe entire cycle is orchestrated by `G1Policy` (src/hotspot/share/gc/g1/g1Policy.{hpp,cpp}), which makes heuristic decisions about when to start marking, when to transition to mixed phase, and how aggressively to collect old regions based on heap occupancy and collection time targets."
